B8 — Scheduler (APScheduler)

Add apscheduler to requirements.txt. Build app/tasks/scheduler.py.
Use APScheduler with BackgroundScheduler. On app startup (FastAPI lifespan event), load all enabled tasks from task store and register them as jobs based on their schedule_type:

every_15_min → IntervalTrigger(minutes=15)
every_1_hour → IntervalTrigger(hours=1)
daily → CronTrigger(hour=HH, minute=MM) using the task's daily_time
adhoc → do not register (run only on manual trigger)

Each scheduled job calls TaskExecutor(task).run().
Expose functions: register_task(task), unregister_task(task_id), trigger_task_now(task_id) — this is what the "Run Now" button calls.
Wire to the tasks router:

POST /api/tasks/:id/run — calls trigger_task_now(task_id). Returns {run_id, status: "triggered"} immediately (do not wait for completion — run in background thread).
When a task is toggled off (PATCH /api/tasks/:id/toggle → enabled=False): call unregister_task.
When toggled on: call register_task.
When a task is created with a non-adhoc schedule: auto-register it.
When a task is deleted: unregister it.

On app shutdown (lifespan end): call scheduler.shutdown().


